A  key ingredient in $W[R,L,U]$ is  the $(2n-2)$-form     $S_{2n-2}$.  This form    is  the  ``Bardeen counterterm''  that was originally introduced  by W.~Bardeen  to ensure that the ``consistent anomaly'' vanished for vector currents. Here it must be included in the action  for a rather different reason:   the left and right Dirac seas are being glued together by the single mass-generating field multiplet $U$ \cite{manes}. 






